BREAKING: #Italy Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte just announced the extension of the #coronavirus lockdown until May 3. The lockdown, which has been in place since March 9, was due to end on April 13.
Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte has announced the extension of Italy’s nationwide #coronavirus #lockdown until May 3.

“If we weaken now, we risk everything.” By May 3rd there will be another evaluation about relaxing the lockdown conditions. “We need to wait.” But some shops (bookstores and forestry) will open April 14. #coronavirus #Conte @ABC
